.TH "dpni_set_buffer_layout" 9 "dpni_set_buffer_layout" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dpni_set_buffer_layout \- Set buffer layout configuration.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dpni_set_buffer_layout
.BI "(struct fsl_mc_io *mc_io "  ","
.BI "u32 cmd_flags "  ","
.BI "u16 token "  ","
.BI "enum dpni_queue_type qtype "  ","
.BI "const struct dpni_buffer_layout *layout "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mc_io" 12
Pointer to MC portal's I/O object
.IP "cmd_flags" 12
Command flags; one or more of 'MC_CMD_FLAG_'
.IP "token" 12
Token of DPNI object
.IP "qtype" 12
Type of queue this configuration applies to
.IP "layout" 12
Buffer layout configuration
.SH "RETURN"
'0' on Success; Error code otherwise.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fIwarning\fP     Allowed only when DPNI is disabled
